AddCarButtonComponent.name: AddCarButtonComponent

Presents 'add new car' button that links
to addCar view'

AddCarComponent.name: AddCarComponent
AddCarComponent.description: Presents form for adding new car

ProfileComponent.name: ProfileComponent
ProfileComponent.description:
Displays user profile form for viewing and changing
user profile data.

SignInComponent.name: SignInComponent
SignInComponent.description: Handles sign-in process by displaying and managing sign-in form

SignUpComponent.name: SignUpComponent
SignUpComponent.description: Handles sign up by displaying and managing sign-up form

AuthModule.name: AuthModule
AuthModule.description: Contains all the authentication and user profile functionality.

FillUpsComponent.name: FillUpsComponent
FillUpsComponent.description: Handles fill ups for selected car, inside accordion component

EditCarComponent.name: EditCarComponent
EditCarComponent.description: Presents form for editing a car

AddFillUpComponent.name: AddFillUpComponent
AddFillUpComponent.description: Controls the form for adding a fill up

EditFillUpComponent.name: EditFillUpComponent
EditFillUpComponent.description: Controls the form for editing a fill up

FillUpDetailComponent.name: FillUpDetailComponent
FillUpDetailComponent.description:
Shows all the details of the selected fill up
Also handles deletion of a fill up

FillUpsListEntryComponent.name: FillUpsListEntryComponent
FillUpsListEntryComponent.description: Displays single entry in fill ups list

FillUpsListComponent.name: FillUpsListComponent
FillUpsListComponent.description: Displays a vertical list of fill ups for the selected car

AddReminderComponent.name: AddReminderComponent
AddReminderComponent.description: Controls the form for adding a reminder

EditReminderComponent.name: EditReminderComponent
EditReminderComponent.description: Controls the form for editing a reminder

RemindersListEntryComponent.name: RemindersListEntryComponent
RemindersListEntryComponent.description: Shows an individual reminder in the reminders list

RemindersListComponent.name: RemindersListComponent
RemindersListComponent.description:
Shows a list of all reminder by using RemindersListEntry component for individual reminders
It also handles add reminder click and deletion of the selected reminder

RemindersComponent.name: RemindersComponent
RemindersComponent.description:
A container component for reminders accordion sub-view
Fetches reminder data for all other reminder components

CarsListComponent.name: CarsListComponent
CarsListComponent.description:
This component displays the list of all the cars by iterating
cars array and sending each car to car component
for display

CarDetailViewComponent.name: CarDetailViewComponent
CarDetailViewComponent.description: This component is a view wrapper for car detail view

ChromeComponent.name: ChromeComponent
ChromeComponent.description:
The chrome of the whole application
Shows status bar at the top of the screen and car data below

AuthService.name: AuthService
AuthService.description: Performs actual authentication operations used by auth module and elsewhere

DataService.name: DataService
DataService.description:
Provides exchange of data with a back-end database
via the HTTP server. Three collections are implemented:
cars, fillups and reminders, with CRUD methods for each.
Caching is implemented for all the collections.
A single method handles eventual errors.

NotificationHubService.name: NotificationHubService
NotificationHubService.description:
This service is notification hub for the application
It exposes a method which any part of code can use to emit an event
And any component can subsribe to listen to events emitted from the hub

UtilitiesService.name: UtilitiesService
UtilitiesService.description:
Contains common utilities services such as handling errors
and different calculations used on several places in the app

CarComponent.name: CarComponent
CarComponent.description:
This component shows a car card, which displays car name and model, car avatar, 
three navigational buttons and three fields with basic statistics

CarsComponent.name: CarsComponent
CarsComponent.description:
This component displays all the cars by iterating
cars array and sending each car to car component
for display

CompleteRegistrationComponent.name: CompleteRegistrationComponent
CompleteRegistrationComponent.description: This component displays the complete registration form

SummaryComponent.name: SummaryComponent
SummaryComponent.description: This component displays the Mileage Stats summary pane

CarsDataResolve.name: CarsDataResolve
CarsDataResolve.description: Fetches cars data for car cards

FillUpsDataResolve.name: FillUpsDataResolve
FillUpsDataResolve.description: Fetches fill ups data for a car

StatusBarComponent.name: StatusBarComponent
StatusBarComponent.description: Component for showing application state in the status bar

WellcomeComponent.name: WellcomeComponent
WellcomeComponent.description: Shows 'wellcome, <user>' message in the status bar

classitems.description:
This method accepts an User parameter
and uses http to PUT an User object to update the server-side database.
It returns server response as a Promise, or rejects as an error message
or an error object if error message doesn't exist
classitems.name: updateUser

return.description: Server response

classitems.description:
This method accepts no parameters and uses http to GET
all the Cars of a user from the server. It returns a Promise resolved
as an array of Cars, or rejected as an error message or
an error object if error message doesn't exist
classitems.name: getCars

return.description: The array of Cars as a Promise

classitems.description:
This method accepts a single integer parameter, an id for a Car,
and uses it to http GET the corresponding Car data.
It returns a Promise resolved as a Car object,
or rejected as an error message or an error object
if error message doesn't exist
classitems.name: getCarById

return.description: Car object as a Promise

classitems.description:
This method accepts a Car parameter and base64 encoded image
and uses http to POST new  Car to the server-side database.
It returns a Promise resolved as a Car object,
or rejected as an error message or
an error object if error message doesn't exist
classitems.name: addCar

return.description: Added Car as a Promise

classitems.description:
This method accepts a Car parameter and base64 encoded image
and uses http to PUT a Car object to update the server-side database.
It returns server response as a Promise, or rejects as an error message
or an error object if error message doesn't exist
classitems.name: updateCar

return.description: Server response

classitems.description:
This method accepts a parameter of number type and uses http to DELETE Car 
of this id from the server-side database. It returns a Promise resolved
as server response object, or rejected as an error message or
an error object if error message doesn't exist
classitems.name: deleteCar

params.name: carId
params.description: Car.id of the Car object to delete

return.description: Server response as a promise

classitems.description:
This method accepts car id as a parameter and uses http
to GET all the Fillups for a Car. It returns a Promise
resolved as an array of FillUps,
or rejected as an error message or an error object
if error message doesn't exist
classitems.name: getFillUps

classitems.description:
This method accepts two parameters, an id for a Fill Up,
and an id for a car. It uses http GET to fetch the corresponding
Fillup for a Car.
It returns a Promise resolved as a FillUp object,
or rejected as an error message or an error object
if error message doesn't exist
classitems.name: getFillUpById

params.name: carId
params.description: id of a Car to which a fill up belongs to

return.description: The FillUp for a Car as a Promise

classitems.description:
This method accepts no parameters and returns an object containing
arrays of all fill ups for all the cars. Object keys are car ids, and
values are arrays of Fill Ups. Method returns a Promise 
which on error is rejected as an error message or an error object
if error message doesn't exist
classitems.name: getAllFillUps

classitems.description:
This method accepts a car id and a FillUp object as a parameter and uses
http POST to add a fill up to a Car. It returns a Promise resolved
to a FillUp object, or rejected as an error message or an error object
if error message doesn't exist
classitems.name: addFillUp

params.name: carId
params.description: Id of the car to which the new fill up is to be added

return.description: The FillUp added as a Promise

classitems.description:
This method accepts car Id and a FillUp object as parameters
and uses http to PUT updated FillUp to the database.
It returns server response as a Promise on success,
or rejected as an error message or an error object
if error message doesn't exist
classitems.name: updateFillUp

return.description: The server response, as a Promise

classitems.description:
This method accepts car.id and FillUp.id as parameters and deletes the corresponding
entry in the database using http DELETE. It returns server response as a Promise
on success, and rejects with an error message or an error object
if error message doesn't exist
classitems.name: deleteFillUp

params.name: carId
params.description: id of the car to which fill up belongs to

params.name: fillUpId
params.description: id of the FillUp to be deleted

return.description: The deleted FillUp

classitems.description:
This method accepts car id as a parameter and returns all reminders
of a car by issuing a http GET request. It returns an array
of Reminder objects as a Promise. On error it rejects
with an error message, or an error object if error message doesn't exist
classitems.name: getReminders

return.description: All the reminders of a car as a Promise

classitems.description:
This method accepts two parameters, an id for a Reminder,
and an id for a car. It uses http GET to fetch the corresponding
Reminder for a Car.
It returns a Promise resolved as a Reminder object,
or rejected as an error message or an error object
if error message doesn't exist
classitems.name: getReminderById

return.description: The Reminder for a Car as a Promise

classitems.description:
This method accepts no parameters and returns an object containing
arrays of all reminders for all the cars. Object keys are car ids, and
values are arrays of Reminders. Method returns a Promise 
which on error is rejected as an error message or an error object
if error message doesn't exist
classitems.name: getAllReminders

classitems.description:
This method accepts a parameter of Reminder type and calls http to POST this new Reminder
to a database. It returns a Promise resolved as the added Reminder on success, and on
error it returns error message or an error object if error message doesn't exist
classitems.name: addReminder

return.description: Promise<Reminder> The added Reminder

classitems.description:
This method accepts car Id and a Reminder object as parameters
and uses http to PUT updated Reminder to the database.
It returns server response as a Promise on success,
or rejected as an error message or an error object
if error message doesn't exist
classitems.name: updateReminder

return.description: The server response, as a Promise

classitems.description:
This method accepts Reminder.id as a parameter and deletes the corresponding entry
in the database using http DELETE. It returns server response as a Promise 
on success, and rejects with an error message or an error object
if error message doesn't exist
classitems.name: deleteReminder

params.name: reminderId
params.description: id of the Reminder to be deleted

return.description: The deleted Reminder

classitems.description:
This file includes polyfills needed by Angular and is loaded before the app.
You can add your own extra polyfills to this file.

This file is divided into 2 sections:
  1. Browser polyfills. These are applied before loading ZoneJS and are sorted by browsers.
  2. Application imports. Files imported after ZoneJS that should be loaded before your main
     file.

The current setup is for so-called "evergreen" browsers; the last versions of browsers that
automatically update themselves. This includes Safari >= 10, Chrome >= 55 (including Opera),
Edge >= 13 on the desktop, and iOS 10 and Chrome on mobile.

Learn more in https://angular.io/docs/ts/latest/guide/browser-support.html
BROWSER POLYFILLS
Zone JS is required by Angular itself.
APPLICATION IMPORTS

Date, currency, decimal and percent pipes.
Needed for: All but Chrome, Firefox, Edge, IE11 and Safari 10
Need to import at least one locale-data with intl.
